FBIS3-31378 "dreeu033__a94004" FBIS-EEU-94-033-A Document Type:Daily Report 17 February 1994 ANNEX Bulgaria Army Chief of Staff on Threat of Air Strikes AU1602093894 Sofia BTA in English 2308 GMT 15 Feb 94 AU1602093894 Sofia BTA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Sofia, February 15 (BTA) -- "In my opinion any statements that possible airstrikes against Bosnia pose no threat to stability and security in this region are unacceptable and naive," Army General Lyuben Petrov, chief of the General Staff of the Bulgarian Army, told the press today. He described as correct, clear and consistent Bulgaria's policy as stated by President Zhelyu Zhelev, for noninvolvement in military measures and no form of support for other countries' intervention and no air corridors to be used by countries that choose to get involved in the conflict.
